    <thetext>Description of problem:

The /usr/lib64/firefox/browser/defaults/preferences/firefox-redhat-default-prefs.js now has

/* Allow sending credetials to all https:// sites */
pref(&quot;network.negotiate-auth.trusted-uris&quot;, &quot;https://&quot;)

Sadly, it is not used because the pref line is missing ending semicolon.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):

firefox-47.0-4.fc24.x86_64

How reproducible:

Deterministic.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Use the latest Firefox.
2. Open about:config, find trusted-uris.
3. Hit right click + Reset.

Actual results:

The default value is empty string and attempt to authenticate to Negotiate-covered website works (SSO).

Expected results:

The default value is https:// and attempt to authenticate to Negotiate-covered website fails.

Additional info:</thetext>
